ullo and demands a tribute from the king of the Ahl-Agullo and references that its planet's greatest warrior and son is dead. Corvus Glaive then reveals that the last time his master came to this world, he burned this world down and asks the king to pay a tribute. Returning to his master, Corvus Glaive gives his master Ahl-Agullo's tribute and asks if this tribute pleases him. Corvus' master, Thanos, replies \"yes\". The tribute is revealed to be a crate containing the severed heads of many Ahl-Agullo citizens.<ref>''Free Comic Book Day Vol 2013 Infinity''</ref>\n\nCorvus Glaive and the rest of the Black Order (which also consisted of Black Dwarf, Ebony Maw, [[Proxima Midnight]], and Supergiant) arrive on Earth and appeared at the different parts of the Earth to confront the [[Illuminati (comics)|Illuminati]]. Corvus Glaive and Supergiant arrived at the [[X-Mansion|Jean Grey School for Higher Learning]].<ref>''New Avengers'' Vol. 3 #8</ref>\n\nAfter the Inhumans deny a tribute to Corvus Glaive, Thanos appears on [[Attilan]] to meet with [[Black Bolt]]. Black Bolt attacks Thanos with his hypersonic voice.<ref>''Infinity'' #3</ref>\n\nThe event ended with the defeat of Thanos's forces and the capture of Thanos and his generals Proxima Midnight and Corvus Glaive, all three of whom were imprisoned in amber in \"a state of living death\" by Thanos's son Thane.<ref>''Infinity'' #6</ref> They joined the [[Black Swan (comics)|Black Swan]] and [[Terrax|Terrax the Enlightened]] as Illuminati prisoners.{{issue|date=July 2014}} They were later freed by [[Namor]] and formed the new [[Cabal (comics)|Cabal]].<ref>''New Avengers'' Vol. 3 #23</ref>\n\n==Powers and abilities==\nCorvus Glaive has enhanced strength, speed, durability, and endurance.\n\nIt is also shown that as long as his blade remains whole, Corvus Glaive cannot die.<ref>''New Avengers'' Vol. 3 #9</ref>\n\n==In other media==\n\n===Video games===\n* Corvus Glaive appears in ''[[Marvel: Avengers Alliance]]''. He appears in Spec-Ops #13 which is based on the ''Infinity'' storyline.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Marvel Comics supervillains]]\n\n\n{{Marvel-villain-stub}}"}]}}}}